  Based on the novel by Edgar Allan Poe
 
  1827: William Legrand, the son of a ruined family, has fled to Sullivan's
  Island, North Carolina, to escape his shame. There he discovers a solid gold
  beetle and carefully picks it up in a sheet of parchment. That night, he
  draws the beetle on the same sheet of parchment; the heat of his hands
  reveals a series of symbols written in invisible ink! William believes that
  he has found cryptic instructions that will reveal the hiding place of
  Captain Kidd's lost treasure! Help William find it!
 
  A Thrilling Adventure
 
  Finding the beetle is just the beginning. Help William crack the cryptogram
  left behind by Captain Kidd! If you can solve the message's code, you'll
  find the secret locations on the map. Use your cunning to find the ultimate
  prize... the hidden pirate gold!
